er</i> ‘copper’ (or a Yiddishized form of German <i>Kupfer</i>), hence a metonymic occupational name for a worker or trader in copper or an artificial name."]}]},{"name":"Alice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Alice Cannone Keeper was born about 1565, in Devon, England, United Kingdom. She married Thomas Keeper   AKA Park, Parker and Lee on 7 May 1592, in Uffculme, Devon, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. She died on 2 July 1656, in Uffculme, Devon, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 92."},"et":{"Abt. 1565–8 Oct 1650 OR 2 Jul 1656.   ( both dates state she is a widow,)":"umbes 1565–2. juuli 1656","1562–1638":"1562–1638","1603–Female":"1603–Surnud","1565–1656":"1565–1656","7 May 1592":"7. mai 1592","8 Oct 1650 OR 2 Jul 1656.   ( both dates state she is a widow,)":"2. juuli 1656","1656":"1656","1565":"1565","Abt. 1565":"umbes 1565","1562":"1562","1638":"1638","1603":"1603","Uffculme, Devon (either 8 Oct 1650 OR 2 Jul 1656 - both state 'Widow')":"Uffculme, Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Uffculme, Devon":"Uffculme, Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Uffculme, Devon (Will of 1638 only mentions a Granddaughter, so more likel